20cappuccino-latte%20divide%20became%20a%20masterclass.%20It%20broke%20the%20differences%20into%20texture%2C%20flavor%20balance%2C%20and%20mouthfeel.%20A%20cappuccino%20is%20light%20on%20top%20and%20dense%20underneath%3B%20the%20foam%20%26quot%3Blifts%26quot%3B%20the%20espresso%2C%20sharpening%20its%20flavor.%20A%20latte%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20silkier%20and%20more%20uniform%2C%20with%20milk%20that%20folds%20into%20the%20espresso%20and%20softens%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can%20now%20explain%20my%20coffee%20preference%20with%20something%20more%20informed%20than%20%26quot%3Bit%20tastes%20nicer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263fa5c33-333e-445a-a3ac-b57cd2b124e2%5C%22%3E3.%20Audit%20the%20chatbot's%20memory%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERomaniuk%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-memory-remember-everything-you-ever-told-it-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ememory%20is%20one%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20ChatGPT's%20strengths.%20It%20lets%20the%20model%20infer%20what%20a%20user%20really%20wants%20or%20proactively%20surface%20information%20they%20might%20care%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERomaniuk%20said%20the%20way%20to%20stay%20in%20control%20is%20to%20audit%20what%20the%20model%20remembers%3A%20Delete%20anything%20you%20don't%20want%20it%20holding%20onto%2C%20or%20toggle%20memory%20on%20and%20off%20in%20the%20settings%20so%20the%20chatbot%20only%20draws%20from%20what%20you%20choose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221079%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ChatGPT%20memory%20setting%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693650f071107c9f34577e81%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22764%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUsers%20can%20toggle%20memory%20on%20and%20off%20in%20ChatGPT's%20settings.%3Cp%3ELee%20Chong%20Ming%2FChatGPT%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20something%20I've%20been%20doing.%20I%20don't%20turn%20memory%20off%20because%20most%20of%20what%20I%20share%20ends%20up%20being%20useful%20later.%20But%20I%20do%20clear%20out%20meaningless%20or%20throwaway%20chats%20so%20they%20don't%20clutter%20things%20or%20muddy%20what%20the%20model%20learns%20about%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20paid%20off.%20ChatGPT%20now%20understands%20me%20as%20a%20journalist%20who%20interviews%20AI%20founders%20by%20day%20and%20trains%20for%20fitness%20races%20after%20hours.%20It%20answers%20like%20it%20knows%20I'm%20just%20as%20likely%20to%20ask%20about%20model%20behavior%20as%20I%20am%20about%20Hyrox%20training%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225ffe4e02-c877-412d-b676-4d587504badf%5C%22%3E4.%20Ask%20ChatGPT%20to%20improve%20prompts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKim%20said%20users%20can%20ask%20ChatGPT%20to%20help%20come%20up%20with%20better%20prompts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20needed%20to%20understand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-invest-xlight-chip-startup-former-intel-semiconductor-race-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efree-electron%20lasers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20help%20create%20the%20high-energy%20light%20sources%20behind%20semiconductor%20manufacturing%20(for%20journalism%2C%20of%20course).%20Instead%20of%20pretending%20I%20knew%20what%20to%20ask%2C%20I%20asked%20ChatGPT%20what%20questions%20I%20should%20be%20asking%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20responded%20with%20a%20set%20of%20%26quot%3Bhigh-leverage%20questions%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20grouped%20from%20foundational%20to%20research-level%20%E2%80%94%20that%20showed%20me%20exactly%20how%20to%20think%20about%20the%20technology.%20For%20someone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnon-technical-people-vibecoding-lessons-ai-apps-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewithout%20much%20technical%20background%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20framing%20was%20helpful.%20ChatGPT%20was%20teaching%20me%20how%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarc-andreessen-how-to-prompt-ai-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eask%20smarter%20questions%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a628cba-8a85-4cbe-b26d-2a92f2a5e994%5C%22%3E5.%20Switch%20through%20personality%20modes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERomaniuk%20said%20she%20switches%20between%20ChatGPT's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-chatgpt51-new-personalities-answered-the-same-prompts-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epersonality%20modes%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Ball%20the%20time%26quot%3B%20to%20understand%20how%20each%20one%20feels.%20It's%20part%20of%20her%20job%20shaping%20model%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20her%20favorites%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bnerd%26quot%3B%20mode%2C%20which%20gives%20the%20model%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20exploratory%20response%20style%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20a%20good%20cynic%2C%20so%20I%20asked%20ChatGPT%20in%20%26quot%3Bcynical%20mode%26quot%3B%20to%20explain%20embodied%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20move%20my%20work%20forward%2C%20but%20the%20explanation%20made%20me%20laugh%3A%20%26quot%3BEmbodied%20intelligence%20is%20one%20of%20those%20tech%20terms%20people%20throw%20around%20like%20everyone%20has%20a%20robotics%20Ph.D.%20hiding%20under%20their%20bed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20in%20AI%20land%20obsess%20over%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c789f6b4-4e36-4881-a278-846a9fc7f3f3%5C%22%3E6.%20Retry%20tasks%20regularly%20and%20'pressure-test'%20the%20model%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERomaniuk%20said%20she%20likes%20to%20%26quot%3Bpressure%20test%26quot%3B%20the%20model%20%E2%80%94%20pushing%20it%20to%20its%20limits%20to%20see%20how%20it's%20changing%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20something%20that%20couldn't%20work%20now%2C%20it%20might%20work%20in%20three%20months'%20time.%20%26quot%3BJust%20keep%20at%20it%2C%20keep%20playing%2C%20keep%20trying%2C%26quot%3B%20Romaniuk%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20%26quot%3Bpressure%20testing%26quot%3B%20the%20model%20through%20my%20Korean%20studies%2C%20regularly%20throwing%20it%20prompts%20that%20stretch%20its%20ability%20to%20break%20down%20the%20language.%20I've%20spent%20months%20asking%20ChatGPT%20to%20teach%20me%20grammar%2C%20extract%20vocabulary%20from%20worksheets%2C%20and%20explain%20unfamiliar%20sentence%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20versions%20often%20pulled%20out%20the%20wrong%20words%20or%20mixed%20up%20written%20forms.%20Now%2C%20it%20parses%20text%20accurately%2C%20distinguishes%20between%20formal%20and%20polite%20forms%2C%20and%20explains%20grammar%20in%20clear%2C%20beginner-friendly%20steps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tips%20made%20my%20use%20of%20ChatGPT%20feel%20more%20intentional.%20Some%20effects%20were%20small%2C%20others%20more%20striking%2C%20but%20they%20certainly%20nudged%20the%20model%20to%20reveal%20more%20of%20what%20it%20can%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-staff-6-tips-chatgpt-model-smarter-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1765168238000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69329bce04d0f0a114f17713%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-staff-6-tips-chatgpt-model-smarter-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22OpenAI%20staff%20shared%20six%20tips%20for%20using%20ChatGPT%20better.%20I%20tested%20them%2C%20and%20several%20noticeably%20improved%20my%20experience.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cmlee%40insider.com%20(Lee%20Chong%20Ming)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-staff-6-tips-chatgpt-model-smarter-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Korea%20Box%20Office%3A%20%E2%80%98Zootopia%202%E2%80%99%20Leads%20as%20%E2%80%98People%20Upstairs%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Jujutsu%20Kaisen%E2%80%99%20Debut%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1765168188000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvar